modules.description: Handles reading from and writing to input and output channels using strings and buffers. Provides functions for efficiently transferring data between channels and converting between string and buffer representations. Useful for processing text streams and managing data flow in I/O operations.

Provides functions for safely managing I/O channels, including reading and writing with automatic closure, copying data between channels and files, and redirecting standard input/output. Operates with in_channel, out_channel, and Buffer.t structures. Used to handle file content aggregation, temporary file creation, and stream redirection in I/O-intensive workflows.
